cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new feature ranking method for deep learning models, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper specifically focuses on the interpretability of deep neural networks in healthcare and biological domains, which suggests a stronger connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence. However, the use of clinical time-series data and the application to drug response prediction also suggests a potential connection to computational linguistics and natural language processing.
